radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is hyperemic and dilated measuring up to 10 mm with mild surrounding stranding. No associated fluid collection or free air to suggest perforation. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits, no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion, normal homogenous attenuation in the liver, no focal lesions in the pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and no perinephric abnormality. Unremarkable stomach, small bowel loops normal, urinary bladder and distal ureters unremarkable. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, and no significant atherosclerotic disease noted.
